value.0: Me.. Just a trader who got stuck here by being washed ashore when something happened to my boat.
That is simple... I can not swim.
Ahh the other clans... which would you care to know about.
Are there any left? How quaint!
It is good that they favor stability, otherwise their depredations might outweigh their utility.
Truly, their great passion must be a curse, for Kindred lack the ability to create what they may only impotently observe.
Exercise the wisdom of the ancient kinds when dealing with these vulgar deceivers.
These pitiful creatures still pay the debt earned by their sires so many nights ago, though through no fault of their own.
The price they pay for their supposed enlightenment far exceeds its benefice. Still, learn from them what you may.

For time out of mind have we dueled with the self-styled Keepers. It is a small comfort to see they cannot achieve what we have garnered for ourselves. All the capering and blood-sports in the world cannot disguise inadequacy.

They are as trustworthy and useful as well-bred dogs. We send them forth when it is time for hunting, then call them back to the kennel when more subtle tasks beckon. In this way does everyone fulfil their appointed role.
Their association with serpents is more than appropriate, for their poison infects all whom they taint with their presence. Do not allow them in your domain.
Old wounds scar the Rabble. These hotheads cultivate buried hatreds better than the harpies do. Still, we must be tolerant - centuries of failure must surely be hard to bear.
Nobility once belong to this clan, but they have cast aside their honor in pursuit of wanton diablerie.

Given region we meet often, though our convocations resemble salons or debates and tend to result in more talk than action. Of course, this ponderous discourse is the only "civilized" way to resolve an issue, and impulsive or rash Kindred often chafe under the clan's rigidity. Younger, impatient Ventrue have been known to mount direct challenges to an "old boy's" holdings and position, which is considered the height of treachery and rudeness - unless, of course, the upstart wins.

We have exacting and rarefied tastes, even when it comes to blood. There will be a type of blood that you crave, whether that be no animal, virgin, or young men you will not be able to stray from these tastes even in duress or if your straving.
We hail from professional or high-society stock, lords, ladys, merchant princes, any one of high society. Thus we never Embrace capriciously.

Auspex is a Discipline that grants vampires supernatural senses. It is one of the most common and favored Discipline among Cainites due to its versatility and overall usefulness in just about every facet of vampiric existence. Celerity is a Discipline that grants vampires supernatural speed and finesse by expending vitae. Presence, the discipline of unnatural attraction and emotional control. This discipline is the ultimate exaltation of the "Power of personality" that many kindred have.

Only the best will do. Commonly our havens are in mansions or valuable estates. Being as we often come from wealthy families, and our havens may even be ancestral homes. There's an old Ventrue tradition holds that any member of the clan may take sanctuary with any other member of the clan, and cannot be refused. This tradition is rarely invoked, for the vampire seeking refuge subsequently owes a great debt to the vampire who provided succor. Nonetheless, the custom has saved the unlife of more than one of us.
